cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it as follows."
type: dataset
title: "PRT-Benchmark"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-25"
abstract: >
  PRT-Benchmark is a benchmark of frontier large language model behavior on nine
  formal-methods termination-reasoning task families, evaluated at the minimal
  first-order primitive recursor F(x,y,Z) -> x, F(x,y,S(n)) -> G(y,F(x,y,n)).
  The release covers 27 frontier models and 1,188 sessions, graded on three
  axes (termination, witness adequacy, rule-extracted boundary admissibility)
  against externally-checkable answer keys fixed by archived TTT2/CeTA
  certifications and a companion mechanized Lean 4 theorem stack.
